# Why This Is Still Valuable

Interview question:

> Have you ever faced environment issues while setting up Spark?

Now you'll have a real answer:

> While integrating Spark Structured Streaming with Kafka on Windows, Spark required Hadoop utilities (`winutils.exe`). I configured the Hadoop binaries and environment variables to resolve the issue and successfully connected Spark to Kafka.

That's real engineering work.

---

# Step 1: Create Hadoop Directory

Create:

```text id="fwppaj"
C:\hadoop
```

Inside:

```text id="9n2nsw"
C:\hadoop\bin
```

---

# Step 2: Download winutils.exe

Download a Hadoop 3.x compatible `winutils.exe`.

A commonly used source is the GitHub repository maintained by the community:

```text id="rrnukr"
https://github.com/cdarlint/winutils
```

Navigate to:

```text id="rq9mtu"
hadoop-3.3.6/bin
```

Download:

```text id="6htxaq"
winutils.exe
```

Place it in:

```text id="pjqj9j"
C:\hadoop\bin
```

---

# Step 3: Set Environment Variables

Open PowerShell as Administrator:

```powershell id="38t6w2"
setx HADOOP_HOME "C:\hadoop" /M
```

Then:

```powershell id="3m7xhf"
setx hadoop.home.dir "C:\hadoop" /M
```

Restart PowerShell afterward.

---

# Step 4: Verify

Run:

```powershell id="s1nfwj"
echo $env:HADOOP_HOME
```

Expected:

```text id="1uvrhi"
C:\hadoop
```

---

